FBIS4-36790 "drnes114_k_94003" FBIS-NES-94-114 Daily Report 10 Jun 1994 IRAQ Radio Cites UK Paper on Saddam's Health Radio Cites UK Paper on Saddam's Health NC1006153094 (Clandestine) Voice of Iraqi Islamic Revolution in Arabic 1430 GMT 10 Jun 94 NC1006153094 (Clandestine) Voice of Iraqi Islamic Revolution in Arabic 1430 GMT 10 Jun 94 Arabic BFN [Text] The British DAILY EXPRESS newspaper on Wednesday 2 June 1994 reported that tyrant Saddam has been undergoing extensive medical observation for some time due to his serious heart condition. The newspaper said that recently he has been frequently slipping into a coma because of the weak blood flow from his heart to his brain. The paper noted that the Baghdad tyrant has not made any public appearances due to his critical medical condition.
